	   <tr><td colspan=2> Also, as long as you're getting that buff from your local shaman, why not have him summon a weight-reducing bag for you? I don't think many people know of this, and I can't remember what they're called, but I'm sure most shamans would be willing to do this and it'll help you a little with your day's loot.<br> I also use my sewing kit as a container. I know there was some talk of changing these so anything in them would disappear at the end of the day, but they haven't changed it as of yet. Each kit weighs only .4, and even if the stuff didn't stay overnight, you could put it in the regular inventory slots when you camp. It's nice to have an 8 slot low-weight box as long as you don't press 'combine' :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
