	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes indeed...Both the spirit pouch and a dimension posket from a Mage are great...as long as you don't go LD too...<br><br>Sewing kits are a great way to hold down weight, but you can also use cooking spits...they cost less to buy and are 6 slot but weigh in at .2.<br><br>You can carry less, but your base weight goes down...seems a pretty fair trade off...<br><br>Nice thing about the spit (or sewing kit) is that you can practice some trade skills during down time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cooking is and excellent skill as food you make weighs .1.  Downside is the ingredients (except for meat you acquire from kills) makes it more expensive than just buying muffins...<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
